86.1	Indira_Gandhi	Indira Gandhi	Indira Priyadarshini Gandhi , née Nehru; 19 November 1917 – 31 October 1984) was an Indian politician who served as the third Prime Minister of India for three consecutive terms (1966–77) and a fourth term (1980–84). Gandhi was the second female head of government in the world after Sirimavo Bandaranaike of Sri Lanka, and she remains as the world's second longest serving female Prime Minister as of 2012. She was the first woman to become prime minister in India.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7d/Indira2.jpg/200px-Indira2.jpg
